    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "that makes sense. i've seen some people say the UN is basically just a relic of the post-WWII era that's totally incapable of handling modern stuff like cyber warfare or non-state actors. is that a common view among historians, or is that just more of a political critique?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
