      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "That view is a very common and increasingly robust argument among critical international relations scholars. They argue that the UN's foundational architecture, designed for state-centric conflicts, is inherently ill-equipped to manage transnational threats like cyber warfare or the rise of sophisticated non-state actors. In essence, the institution's bureaucratic and diplomatic framework struggles to adapt to the speed and nature of 21st-century global challenges.",
